{
  "texts": [
    "OPT-66B was significantly better than the smaller OPT models, but still substandard given its size.",
    "OPT-IML 30B and Galactica 30B with 18.2% and 12.7% respectively, were also rather disappointing.",
    "We could not produce usable results with LLaMA 65B, which may point to an erroneous checkpoint being leaked / published.The 70B parameter model Luminous Supreme from the German startup Aleph Alpha performs similar to OPT-66B with 30% accuracy.",
    "In June, a new version of it called \"control\" was published that increased this result to 41.8%, which is still below the best 7B parameter models.After the publishing of QLora in May 2023 [46], a lot of new instruction-tuned models with 30B parameters and more were published.",
    "This pushed the previously low average score of the largest models significantly."
  ]
}